Right from the first episode this one grabbed me and would not let me go until I'd watched the very last episode and even then not until I'd watched the whole thing a second time just to make sure I hadn't missed anything. From the gorgeous sets and characters to the creative story lines, from the profound revelations to the fact that almost no assumption you will make is what really happened, this series is surprising, endearing and utterly amazing.<br /><br />As an American who doesn't speak a word of Korean I was still able to thoroughly enjoy this epic sweeping tale of drama, comedy, romance, loss, tragedy, penance, redemption, comradery and so much more (though the first time through I did use 10 sec. rewind a LOT to be able to absorb some of the longer subtitling).
