Imagine your favorite historical mini-series (usually 6-8 episodes), the one where you wanted it to slow down so you could drink in the beauty of the costumes, scenery, hairstyles and decorations; where you were so sad because it was over?  Now imagine you get it all.. every detail, nuance and 'how did they do that'? I cannot tell you how many times I hit pause to admire set decoration, elaborate hair and amazing clothing. 87 episodes and I never tired of it even a little bit.  The story itself is beautiful, tragic, triumphant, devastating and oddly hopeful and quite likely a true depiction of the very real dangers inside an Imperial Court.  I have never shed so many tears and yet, I will be forever grateful I saw this one!
This may be the best series I've ever seen!
